Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.11,0:00:02.43,main,Tsubame,0000,0000,0000,,How's it look?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:02.43,0:00:04.46,main,Midori,0000,0000,0000,,A little crooked on the right.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.46,0:00:05.66,main,Midori,0000,0000,0000,,Too far.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.66,0:00:06.98,main,Midori,0000,0000,0000,,There! Perfect!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.57,0:00:10.54,main,Midori,0000,0000,0000,,Now that is quite the sight.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.70,0:00:19.99,main,Tsubame,0000,0000,0000,,It looks good!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.33,0:00:22.29,main,Midori,0000,0000,0000,,Studio...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.29,0:00:23.79,main,Both,0000,0000,0000,,Eizouken!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.29,0:00:23.79,sign_535_9_Film,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,Film
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.79,0:00:24.79,sign_571_10_Film,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,Film
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.66,0:00:30.55,main,Midori,0000,0000,0000,,What if we had the logo walk by at the \Nbeginning of every project, like this?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.55,0:00:32.20,main,Tsubame,0000,0000,0000,,I love it!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.20,0:00:34.93,main,Kanamori,0000,0000,0000,,We don't even have a project yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.72,0:00:38.34,main,Tsubame,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, there you are, Kanamori—
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.34,0:00:40.76,main,Kanamori,0000,0000,0000,,Didn't I tell you two not \Nto get ahead of yourselves?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.76,0:00:42.35,main,Tsubame,0000,0000,0000,,But since we've got a meeting place—
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.35,0:00:44.94,sign_535_9_Film,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,{\c&HAA9E9E&\3c&HFFFFFF&}Film
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.35,0:00:44.94,main,Kanamori,0000,0000,0000,,It just looks like a random \Nsign that says "film."
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.94,0:00:47.16,main,Midori,0000,0000,0000,,A good design is about paying attention \Nto the minute details that—
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.16,0:00:48.21,main,Kanamori,0000,0000,0000,,More importantly...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.21,0:00:52.47,main,Kanamori,0000,0000,0000,,We need to fix up the building \Nand then get to some actual work.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.47,0:00:55.95,main,Kanamori,0000,0000,0000,,Because otherwise, our little \Ngroup is going to be broken up.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.95,0:00:59.14,main,Midori,0000,0000,0000,,Hang on! The eizouken\N only just came together!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.14,0:01:01.85,main,Kanamori,0000,0000,0000,,Do you think we have\N all the time in the world?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.85,0:01:04.92,main,Kanamori,0000,0000,0000,,After a certain someone \Nspilled the beans about our
Dialogue: 0,0:01:04.92,0:01:06.94,main,Kanamori,0000,0000,0000,,anime production to a teacher?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.94,0:01:09.94,main,Midori,0000,0000,0000,,No way... I thought you \Nconvinced him to back down!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.94,0:01:13.29,main,Kanamori,0000,0000,0000,,Are you getting enough \Noxygen to your brain?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:13.29,0:01:16.38,main,Kanamori,0000,0000,0000,,My arguments were all just to get \Nhim to back off for the time being.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:16.38,0:01:19.70,main,Kanamori,0000,0000,0000,,If he thinks about it calmly, \Nhe'll realize that we don't have a case.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.54,0:01:24.29,main,Kanamori,0000,0000,0000,,My point being, if you don't \Nwant to take that sign down,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:21.22,0:01:26.73,sign_1948_31_Film,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,Film
Dialogue: 0,0:01:24.29,0:01:26.73,main,Kanamori,0000,0000,0000,,we need to accomplish something.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.73,0:01:32.98,sign_571_10_Film,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,{\t(1358,2734,\c&H9DAA9B&\3c&H3A211E&\4c&HEDFEFD&)}Film
